Name: Bernie's Beach Bar
reviews: [{'author_name': 'Kelly Gallagher', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107077819701241747126/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJzEG9DkZJKUY1kh6urEZPhXwxm5oGl8p_VSqJYG=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': 'Make sure you know ahead of time if you are drinking a drink at the bar near corn hole. Mahi Tacos were okay, seasoning rub on the sirloin kind of ruined the steak for us - would prefer it more plain. Overall great for views and drinks, food is slightly secondary. Name: The Goat
reviews: [{'author_name': 'Dave Allison', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110893157938228247635/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJxwVfJUvq4EFgwY_sp1iaNk8xEOHvm6NmkMf7zA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a week ago', 'text': "Let me start by saying the food was good his and served quickly.  The reason for the 3 star review was the waitress.  We were there on 2 for 1 burger night.  We order 6 burgers among the 5 of us; 5 specialty burgers and one build your own.  We also just ordered water. As I said at the top we enjoyed our food.  When we got the bill,  I was confused.  We were charge for 4 of the burgers instead of 3 and there was a charge for 5 sodas.  It turns out that the 2 for 1 is only on the specialty burgers and it is also a requirement to order a drink. Our waitress failed to inform us of these restrictions.  I don't mind that they exist,  but she should have told us.  The build your own burgers was,  essentially,  the TV12 specialty burger ( just cheese). She really should have either made that adjustment automatically or informed us that the build your own didn't qualify for the 2 for 1. Same with the drinks.  She should have told us we were going to get charged anyway so we could have ordered something other than water since we were paying for it. Lastly, she never came back to ask if we needed any refills on our waters and when we asked we had to ask twice a she didn't bring any refills the first time we asked.", 'time': 1655862264}, {'author_name': 'Benedict Christen', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110403977123196825222/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Giw-xrc1-xn3mLZYW_ssr2qQKMt8ZmkzfibcYtLTA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'We‚Äôve been going to the Goat Portsmouth for a few years now, and this past weekend reminded us why we love it so much.  We had a large party of 12 which isn‚Äôt easy for a busy restaurant like the goat to accommodate considering we weren‚Äôt all showing up at the same time. Name: The Press Room
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Paul Delabruere', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106677551174586576333/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiNsPJMzK7e8gTkqojVZUmzmuzYYWsJQGs86frqTg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': "This bar is extremely cool. The live shows are very interesting, but we haven't been to one yet. The space is very comfortable and handsome. The food and cocktail menu are full of fascinating options, and I would love to come back regularly and try them all. They use house made infusions and flavored salts, kimchi, etc. Our waiter was awesome. He was very attentive but also very laid back, and made us feel comfortable taking our time, even on a busy night.", 'time': 1651338001}, {'author_name': 'Covering New England', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104949038206381565737/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJyrhGjzsZbThC34EiMxNi_h2RGK2HB0XbLrHlDBZQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': "This venue has become one of my favorites to work with and attend. Even at the height of the pandemic - the talent buyer for this venue was responsive, kept me updated and has continued to be a pleasure to work with.   The install of the new sound system from a few year back is perfect for this 125 cap room and its location is clutch!

The food is very good, the vibe is cool, and the diversity of shows they have are great.  In terms of the staff: they have definitely assembled a team of people who get how to run a bar/restaurant/venue of its size.  It's not easy to do and meet all the expectations of others.

I stopped in last week and it appears they have a built in audience that just enjoys being at the Press Room in addition to those that are seeking out certain genres of music or a certain vibe for the evening.

They took a chance recently on having Dueling Pianos (which has been never there) and it was sold out way in advance and it crushed live.  Super interactive, positive, and fun.

The up-and-coming shows to the room are an excellent combination of original music, cover bands, and DJs.  They have something for everyone.

A place like the Press Room is the kind of room you want in every town!  Keep up the good work and thank you.", 'time': 1648645908}, {'author_name': 'Ann Assarsson', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101952330187142778672/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GivoDsh-WsJE7dRXSimbFFPkd87OphQlbtA_qHeXv4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'The upstairs stage and bar level is such a great space, and the bartender was fun and charming! I brought my parents and they had a great time listening to music, and loved the food. Excellent experience and made for a perfect Mothers Day.', 'time': 1652388412}, {'author_name': 'Joshua Corn', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103383479554857791360/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjK39if8v3SP3uW_Y4XDh30SBJeYaFpBq0dxHXOHg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'We tried almost every appetizer and they were all delicious. Bartender never came to our table after giving us the drinks and ran to the other side of the bar when we went to complain to the owner. reviews: [{'author_name': 'Kasey Draper', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115077542804382537927/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJyt1mG0kZ5Nozsf2-nMREg5G2IZ5hrdWcY5AhHr=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Worth the read. We were walking around and celebrating my little sisters 21st birthday. Attempted to go into this place and the ‚Äúsecurity guard‚Äù wouldn‚Äôt let her in on her 21st birthday. Claiming that she ‚Äúcould have been born at 11:59pm today‚Äù meaning she wouldn‚Äôt actually be 21 until the minute she was born, or the following day. Myself and my husband are clearly over 21, not that it even matters. We tried to tell the man, it‚Äôs her 21st birthday, today. He let in countless other people, without question or ID, while examining each of our government issued IDs and embarrassed us, and turned us away for no reason. This is no popular or famous place that we would make an extreme attempt to get in, it‚Äôs a random bar that we walked past. The lack of professionalism and sheer lack of capacity to read the date on a government issued ID was both embarrassing and unnecessary. He felt the need to ridicule us, by letting others in, after us, without question. We were not rude, or unfriendly by any means. We asked the man how is night was going. Only to be turned away based on his lack of reading or misinterpretation of a government issued ID. He told other members of the staff that we were misrepresenting ourselves which is untrue. We had countless positive experiences at other bars in the area. This is the one and only negative experience we had. Which is saying something about the ‚Äúguard‚Äù and the staff at this establishment. reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Joe Young', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106220242837889780438/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJxjpz_uXAazkdwP6yGpNXmI2Tdjj_usINplv2EY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': "I went to a lot of bars in Boston, and this place was easily the worst. Clearly not the best bar in pyongyang yet alone Boston. I was there for the Frozen Four as they decided to host two teams fan bases for the pregame party, except they weren't prepared. Like at all. It was bad, 20 minutes between drinks, surley staff, just plain bad. I get you were overwhelmed but we tipped much better than we should have, and you threatened to shank me (the customer) for having the audacity to expect a drink in under 30 minutes. Personally, I blame the management not the bartender. It was my first day in Boston so I put up with it, but yikes. Go a block over to Sully's where they are prepared, the drinks flow, and no one threatens to kill you and the real Boston fans go. We talked to so many locals who said avoid after the fact, and they were right.

So many better options close to TD Garden, why subject yourself to this place.

Name: Bar 10
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Estefany Yanqui', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104298555553414239006/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJwXQPpeVYsRsw0iDdZFqGEsFOkhS-xekSlSAtbX=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': 'Review is for customer service on behalf of the manager and his team.

We are from out of town and stayed in a hotel down the street for a conference. Choose to get food here for a Rueben sandwich (which is no longer even on their menu). Afterwards, we accidentally left our card in the restaurant.

My partner went in the next morning around ~9am and was told by the service staff that the manager is not available and only he can provide the card. Basically told to come back in later. I didn‚Äôt realize it at the time, but they were just pawning us off for a later problem. We are in a conference so I took a break, left around 1 pm to pick up the card (it‚Äôs a 15 min walk over). The second time around, I was told that ‚Äúthe manager cannot be found‚Äù‚Ä¶.

I knew I wouldn‚Äôt have time later that day to come back so I told them I can wait. Some time goes by and I am approached by the bar tender. She tells me the staff is looking for the manager right now but he‚Äôs in a ‚ÄúVIP meeting with clients selling events‚Äù so he may be hard to find.. I told them I‚Äôll wait cause I don‚Äôt have time to come back later and my flights leaves tomorrow. Some more time passes, the bartender continues to push me to come back later. I insist to wait. Bartender starts to get snarky and told me they can ‚Äúmail me the card‚Äù‚Ä¶ at this point I had enough, that is not costumer service and not even a helpful comment. I explain to her how mailing me a card will not be helpful while I am traveling because it will take 10 business days to arrive. Also why mail a card when my current card is in the restaurant with the manager?? It was very clear she wanted me (the problem) gone.

Finally, the manager was found and was unavailable because he was in a VIP meeting (surprise surprise) and so he relays a message to me via the sou-chef saying he said never found a card. Sou-chef was clearly exacerbated when coming to talk to me as if I have been creating a scene when in actuality I was just not accepting their ‚Äúwe‚Äôll deal with it later‚Äù attitude. . They also told me that security does not have it downstairs‚Ä¶ and again to come back later.

I left. We tried calling the restaurant but no one answers (the phone automatically routes to the managers phone). we ended up calling the Westin Hotel (since the restaurant is actually in the hotel) and they transferred us to house keeping and security. Security told us the card was delivered to them and they have it!!!

Roy Taylor, the operations manager, told us the card was not found so we can leave during his ‚Äúimportant VIP meeting‚Äù. He literally could have just excused himself for LESS THAN 5 MINUTES to address a small issue. This situation was so ridiculously mismanaged. We ended up having to leave the conference AGAIN and walk back to the restaurant for a third time later in the evening. We told the rude bar tender we found the card in security (after she had already told us they checked there and it wasn‚Äôt there)  and all she said was ‚Äúgreat looks like you found it‚Äù. .

If I was considering booking an event, I would NOT consider this location due to the lack of professionalism.
1. The manager did not answer his phone after numerous calls throughout the day.
2. Staff was rude and did not care about the situation
3. Name: Durty Nelly's
reviews: [{'author_name': 'Emily Zambrano', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115303729052125658200/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJzuYebOFmkvVDW3av686OLDSqX3q2MyFXqhzjyY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': 'My sister and I went to this bar upon recommendation. If I could give it a 0/5 I would. I am a server and my sister is a bartender. So we know about the service industry. Here, there was a shortage of everything, but mostly respect. We got to the bar, ordered and received our drinks. At the moment in which we decided to go to the restroom, there were no other women in the bar so we saw best that we accompany each other. While we were in the restroom, a group of boys arrived at the bar. Once we returned to our seats the bartender told us that we couldn‚Äôt go into the restroom together (understandable for men, not so much for women). But we apologized and assured the bartender that we just wouldn‚Äôt use the restroom again.  Then, one of the boys at the bar threw ice at my sister. The bartender did nothing, let him stay. Another patron was the one to say something to the guy that threw the ice. Again, the bartender saw everything. My sister and I decided to leave. It is NOT okay to treat women or ANYONE like this. When I called the establishment my call was answered by the same bartender who claimed he had already ‚Äúspoken‚Äù to these boys, and immediately hung up on me - and didn‚Äôt answer the other times I called to discuss this issue. I can‚Äôt believe that people still act like this and I truly can‚Äôt fathom the fact that nothing was addressed in that moment. Name: Tandy's Pub & Grille
reviews: [{'author_name': 'CiCi', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104531450610226760710/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhhulW4ItfkDgQhfLGgia5LMjHLsYGWBF0Sk6SLpg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': 'I thought I liked Tandy\'s Pub & Grille in Concord. The french fries are great. The happy hour days and times are longer than average (til 9) and the drinks are usually consistent and tasty. I personally haven\'t had any issues or bad experiences with the wait staff or the bartenders. Where Tandy\'s loses any and all credibility is in its annual \'Tandy\'s Idol\' karaoke contest held during the Market Days celebration in downtown Concord each summer. This establishment and its organizer may lie to you and their event sponsors and try to claim that I\'m just a sore loser or bitter ex-contestant - but wrong is wrong and I\'m calling it out. The contest is rigged, probably from the start. I should have realized it in the beginning but I guess I was just trying to RESPECT the competition and the other contestants. That respect was not reciprocated.\nIt was BLATANTLY obvious to me, my family and supporters, the folks in the crowd that approached me afterwards and even the winner\'s OWN MOTHER that the Tandy\'s Idol "fair points system" is just a bunch of crock.\nI would have just let this slide, it seems that that\'s just the way they do things there. But Tandy\'s Idol wasted my time, disrespected my talent, and lied to everyone that participated in that contest and to the crowd that stayed to support the effort. Shame on them for pretending to offer any "honor" to Brian\'s legacy by tainting the idea that they did anything honest and fairly in his name. reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Al Smolkin', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109806018076704114713/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgD9c4IlNEGNeLPT6gRlMwPGI5oSIr4XAr-p9FOYg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'I used to enjoy coming here, but, not anymore.

Last night, I stopped by for a meal and a beer.
After taking my order, the girl bartender never once checked on me whether I'd like a refill, or if my food was to my liking.

What was supposed to be medium-rare steak tips came out of the kitchen cooked at least medium well.
The accompanied salad (prepackaged) was unceremoniously dropped on the bar WITH my food, without even so much as "here's your meal"

Truly, the personal touch extended exec further when the person next to me had to flag the bartender to get me another beer.

If this is the quality of food and service I get for $22 plate of overcooked steak tips and fries, I think I'll spend my money elsewhere.', 'time': 1651905971}, {'author_name': 'Inbound Official', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110442830023032980950/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJx1ghmh_bOrpZyZCES7hKWgSpjrEQH_uqbLjIym=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': 'Steve was an amazing bartender! I ordered a burger cooked very rare and loaded tater tots as well as a whiskey sour. When the food got to my table, I immediately dug in. I took one bite out of the burger before discovering it was completely overcooked, a thick layer of burnt char on the outside and as dry as cardboard on the inside. Not sure if it was just a communication error but I definitely didn't order well-done. I could not even taste any trace of whiskey in my whiskey sour. It simply tasted like lemonade. If I wanted a comparable drink, I would've just gone home and poured myself a glass of minute maid. Awful food and terrible experience all together. A second bartender named Brendan took over towards the tail end of our stay at the Stumble Inn. I explained to him how terrible the food was and how poorly we were treated by our previous bartender and he took my food off the bill which I made sure to leave a good tip for him. [{'author_name': 'Etta Lea', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103606923378791315106/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgkHsWuK5baVxZv6KnFV4AL-Sy12_hXSHBQN_QnIQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a week ago', 'text': 'This review combines our first and second visit experiences.
